You'll find this post in your <code>_posts</code> directory…</pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s10">
    <h2><span class="num">10</span>CLI</h2>
    <p>Three stages, run in order. Each is idempotent and writes to the manifest.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage · jekyll → astro</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> jekyll <span class="fl">--source</span> ./my-jekyll-site <span class="fl">--to</span> ./astro-project
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage transform <span class="fl">--schema</span> content-collections <span class="fl">--content</span> markdown
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--images</span> assets <span class="fl">--redirects</span> netlify</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Values</th><th>Default</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--from</span></td><td><span class="ty">platform</span></td><td><span class="ty">required</span></td><td>Source platform (jekyll).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--source</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td><span class="ty">.</span></td><td>Jekyll project directory.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--to</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td><span class="ty">required</span></td><td>Target Astro project directory.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--include-drafts</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Carry <code>_drafts/</code> as <code>draft: true</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--permalink-style</span></td><td><span class="ty">flat · original · preserve</span></td><td><span class="ty">flat</span></td><td>URL handling strategy — §06.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--content</span></td><td><span class="ty">markdown · mdx</span></td><td><span class="ty">markdown</span></td><td>Body format &amp; Liquid tag handling.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--images</span></td><td><span class="ty">assets · public</span></td><td><span class="ty">assets</span></td><td>Image placement strategy.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--redirects</span></td><td><span class="ty">netlify · vercel · astro</span></td><td><span class="ty">astro</span></td><td>Redirect map format.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--dry-run</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Plan &amp; diff only; write nothing.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s11">
    <h2><span class="num">11</span>Verification</h2>
    <p>Every crossing is auditable. Nothing is written until you've seen what will change.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Dry-run first</strong> — <code>--dry-run</code> prints the full plan and a diff against the target directory; the filesystem is untouched.</li>
      <li><strong>Manifest ledger</strong> — <code>portage.manifest.json</code> records every source file, its checksum, the transform applied (including Liquid tag counts), the output path, and any permalink changes.</li>
      <li><strong>Counted on, counted off</strong> — extract and load counts are reconciled; any delta (skipped drafts, no-output collections, unresolvable Liquid tags) is listed explicitly.</li>
      <li><strong>Idempotent</strong> — re-running over an existing project shows only true changes, so you can re-pull and review before committing.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage load --dry-run</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--dry-run</span>
<span class="out">→ 42 posts → 42 files          ✓ reconciled</span>
<span class="out">→ 5 pages → 5 files            ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 1 collection → 3 documents   ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 86 images → 82 unique        ✓ deduped</span>
<span class="out">→ 38 redirects mapped          ✓ permalink pattern changes</span>
<span class="out">→ 2 no-output collections      ⚠ review — no output:true in config</span>
<span class="out">→ 7 Liquid tags unconverted     ⚠ preserved as HTML comments</span>
<span class="out">→ 0 unresolved references      ✓ nothing left on the dock</span></pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</SpecLayout>
